# ============================================================================
# Without this file, your next commit pushes:
#
#   node_modules/   40,000 files. GitHub rejects the push.
#   .env.local      YOUR SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY.
#
# That key bypasses row-level security entirely. Public on GitHub, anyone can
# download every salon's customer list — thousands of women's names, phone
# numbers, and the times they will be at a known address.
#
# Bots scrape GitHub for exactly this, within minutes of a push.
# ============================================================================

node_modules/
.next/
out/
build/

.env
.env.local
.env*.local

.vercel
*.tsbuildinfo
next-env.d.ts

.DS_Store
*.log
npm-debug.log*

supabase/.temp/
supabase/.branches/

# Never commit a database dump. It is customer PII.
*.dump
*.dump.gpg
*.sql.gpg
